Referencing Figures And Tables. <p>Back to: Caption Main Page</p> <p>Referencing elements in markdown is pretty straight forward. Since this plugin adds a default id to all figures and tables created these ids can be used to reference the element. The following example shows how to reference a figure.</p> <p>Referencing Elements.</p> MarkdownHTML <pre><code>![Caption text](assets/demo.png)

See [Figure](#_figure-1) above for more details.
</code></pre> <pre><code>&lt;figure id=_figure-1&gt;
    &lt;img src="assets/demo.png" alt="This uses the alt as caption" /&gt;
